  "body": "### Description\n\n*Type*: Bug\n*Summary*: entered value persisted in field \"Topic\", but isn't shown after switching to other screen (i.e. after selecting any chat) and come back. It shouldn't be changed OR value should be erased and button \"Join public chat\" should be disabled.\n\nIn fact we can see enabled  \"Join public chat\"  button with empty value in field.\n\n#### Expected behavior\nI see two variants:\n1) input is preserved\n2) input is erased,  \"Join public chat\" button is inactive\n\n#### Actual behavior\ninput is not shown (but not erased)  \"Join public chat\" button is active. If you click on it, new chat with the selected name will be created.\n<img width=\"568\" alt=\"desk_0\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/48209825-5d8d7d80-e376-11e8-826a-e075895de255.png\">\n\n\n### Reproduction\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\n\n- Open Status\n- Log in\n- Click on  +\n- Enter topic name (i.e. #12345)\n- Select any chat from chat list\n- Click on + again\n\n\n### Additional Information\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n* Status version: nightly 08/11/18\n* Operating System: Mac OSx, Linux",
